                  <span class="year">
                    2012                  </span>
                  </p>
                  <h2 class="title"><a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/2012/07/25/the-big-announcement-out-of-brussels/" rel="bookmark">The big announcement out of Brussels</a></h2>

                  <div class="meta">

      				      <p>Published by <a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/author/admin/" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a>  under <a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/category/opinion/europe/" title="View all posts in Europe" rel="category tag">Europe</a>,<a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/category/opinion/" title="View all posts in Opinion" rel="category tag">Opinion</a>,<a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/category/topstories/" title="View all posts in Top Stories" rel="category tag">Top Stories</a> </p>

      			      </div>

      			      <div class="entry">

                    <p>The pressure is building again around the Euro and Euroland. But, this time the response is different. This time there&#8217;s no talk of another summit and another massive &#8220;Rettungspaket&#8221; for countries and/or banks. This time a different wind is blowing around the capitals of Europe.  <a href="http://www.thebigpond.eu/2012/07/25/the-big-announcement-out-of-brussels/#more-5246" class="more-link">[Read on]</a></p>
                  
